channel.description:
<big> **====> ‚ì£—èùìê·∂ú“ú œÉùñã ùê≠‚íΩ·∫∏ ÔΩó—î‚Ç¨–∫** </big>
Welcome to the FIRST Auxy TotW throw down. First, I want to announce a small revamp of the system. If you checked out the TotW hall of fame, you may have already noticed the updated verbiage.
For each five :cd:'s you earn, you are certified gold :dvd:
For each five :dvd:'s you earn, you are certified platinum :minidisc:
Big congratulations to our FIRST gold certified member @simon2! His profile has already been updated. So without any further blibber blabber, read on for the rules.
**‚ì¶hat happens?** > * Each week a new topic (like this one) is posted in the #contests category. > * If you want your track considered for track of the week, just post a link to your track below, before the due date listed at the bottom of this topic. > * The winner will be announced here at the end of the week.
**‚ì°ules:** >1. Track must be made by the submitter, using Auxy. >2. There are no set themes. Any genre. Any tempo. Any automations. >3. Tracks must be 60-seconds or longer. >4. Tracks can't have been posted previously. This competition is for new releases. >5. One entry per person, per week. >6. No collabs or remixes. >7. You can edit your post during the week if you make updates to your submission. >9. External samples can be used for individual instruments or vocals only ie: not sections of sampled music or drum loops. >10. Project files won't be considered. >11. Late entries won't be considered. Enter in the next week instead. >12. Please also create a thread for your track under #tracks, like usual, if you wish.
**‚ìôudging:** One winner is chosen each week, or possibly a draw. Judging will be totally subjective. Please don't ask why your track didn't win. The judges alternate between: -
* iammane * blakkaz * AzureOnyx * MrSerpent * Mr_Mooo * Goxenar * Peregrihn * Dadmother * HexxOfficial
Judge this week is: @iammane
**‚ìürize** * Winner gets a special üíø icon next to their forum name. * Winner's name is also listed in a [winner's thread](https://disco.auxy.co/t/auxy-forum-track-of-the-week-winners/15961).
![Auxy%20Track%20of%20the%20Week|350x350,100%](upload://ia7OKbSnziVU4UHv8vbhMQqNOQx.jpeg) <small>*Logo created by Arimyth </small>
